digraph EpicRunner {
    label="Process all tasks in an epic"
    goal="Implement all child tasks of epic scc-hzj: Two-System Architecture — Security, Data Stewardship, Taste, Variants, and Triage Spine. Implements the five goals of the Two-System Architecture PRD/SPEC (2026-07-16): a security review pass, a data-layer sovereignty system, a codified-taste system, a parallel variant-exploration plugin, and a Foundry-resident triage spine (System 2 v1). All work is built on top of review-panel as the sole diff-review substrate — no phase may introduce a second review mechanism. Five invariants apply across every phase: (1) Substrate rule — any component producing a diff hands it to review-panel (interactive by default, --mode=agent unattended); (2) Dependency direction — triage → review-panel and foundry → {panel, triage} only; review-panel never imports from or special-cases triage; (3) Coverage honesty — every seat/pass that cannot run must report the gap explicitly, never silently skip; (4) Graceful cross-plugin degradation — where one plugin references another, absence degrades to current behavior plus an explicit coverage note; (5) Human artifacts are human-owned — DATA-MODEL.md and TASTE.md are written via human grilling sessions; agents may propose edits but FIX never auto-modifies them. Build order is strictly Phase 1 → 2 → 3 → 4 → 5, with Phase 4 blocked on Phase 3 (taste is the scoring function) and Phase 5 blocked on both Phase 1 and Phase 2 (security seat and data-steward/sovereignty path must exist before triage feeds dependency and migration diffs into the pipeline)."
    model="sonnet"
    timeout="300s"

    start [shape="Mdiamond"]
    done  [shape="Msquare"]

    // --- Pick the next task ---
    pick_task [
        shape="diamond"
        label="Pick Next Task"
        node_type="conditional"
        llm_model="haiku"
        allowed_tools="Bash(bd:*)"
        timeout="120s"
        prompt="Run: bd show scc-hzj
Look at the BLOCKS section to see child tasks.

Then run: bd ready
Find the first ready (unblocked, open) child task of epic scc-hzj.

If you find one:
- Run: bd update <task-id> --status=in_progress
- Write the task ID and full description to .pas/current_task.md
- Respond with MORE on the last line

If all child tasks are closed (no more ready tasks for this epic):
- Respond with DONE on the last line"
    ]

    // --- Investigate ---
    investigate [
        shape="box"
        label="Investigate"
        allowed_tools="Read,Grep,Glob,Bash(bd:*)"
        timeout="600s"
        prompt="Read .pas/current_task.md to get the current task ID and description.
Run bd show <task-id> to get full details.

Investigate the codebase to understand what needs to change:
- Find the relevant files and functions
- Understand the current behavior
- Identify what needs to change

Write your findings to .pas/investigation.md including:
- Files to modify
- Current behavior
- Required changes
- Any risks or dependencies"
    ]

    // --- Implement ---
    implement [
        shape="box"
        label="Implement"
        timeout="900s"
        prompt="Read .pas/current_task.md for the task and .pas/investigation.md for the plan.
Implement the source/doc changes described. Follow existing code patterns and conventions.
Keep changes minimal and focused on the task requirements.

Scope boundary: do NOT create new test fixtures, run live sub-agent dispatches for validation,
or hand-author validation write-ups (e.g. MERGE tables) here, even if investigation.md's plan
calls for them — that work belongs to the Run Tests step, which runs next and owns verification.
If investigation.md already lists such items, leave them for that step; only make the actual
code/doc edits in this node."
    ]

    // --- Test ---
    run_tests [
        shape="box"
        label="Run Tests"
        timeout="1200s"
        prompt="Read .pas/current_task.md to understand what was changed, and .pas/investigation.md
for any fixture/validation work it identified as required by the task's acceptance criteria.

1. If the acceptance criteria require a new test fixture or seeded example, create it now.
2. If they require a live sub-agent dispatch (e.g. via the Task tool) to validate behavior,
   run it now and capture the result.
3. Run the relevant test suite for the modified code. If tests fail, fix the issues and re-run
   until green.
4. If a hand-worked validation write-up (e.g. a MERGE table with fingerprints/confidence
   anchors) is required, author it now.

Write all of the above (test results, fixture summary, live-dispatch output, any write-up) to
.pas/test-results.md."
    ]

    // --- Verify ---
    verify [
        shape="diamond"
        label="Verify"
        node_type="conditional"
        timeout="300s"
        prompt="Read .pas/current_task.md for the task requirements.
Check the changes:
1. Review the git diff
2. Run the linter on changed files
3. Verify tests pass (read .pas/test-results.md)
4. Check that the task's acceptance criteria are met

If everything looks good, respond with PASS on the last line.
If there are problems, respond with FAIL on the last line."
    ]

    fixup [
        shape="box"
        label="Fix Issues"
        timeout="900s"
        prompt="Read .pas/current_task.md and .pas/investigation.md for context.
The verification step found problems. Fix any failing tests, lint errors, or unmet acceptance criteria.
Re-run tests after fixing."
    ]

    // --- Close this task ---
    close_task [
        shape="box"
        label="Close Task"
        allowed_tools="Bash(bd:*),Bash(git:*)"
        timeout="300s"
        prompt="Read .pas/current_task.md to get the task ID.
1. Stage changes: git add -A
2. Commit with a descriptive message referencing the task ID
3. Close the task: bd close <task-id> --reason='Implemented successfully'
4. Run: bd sync --flush-only"
    ]

    // --- Check if more tasks remain ---
    check_remaining [
        shape="diamond"
        label="More Tasks?"
        node_type="conditional"
        llm_model="haiku"
        allowed_tools="Bash(bd:*)"
        timeout="120s"
        prompt="Run: bd show scc-hzj
Look at the BLOCKS section. Count how many child tasks are still open.

Run: bd ready
Check if any remaining child tasks of this epic are ready (unblocked, open).

If there are more ready tasks, respond with MORE on the last line.
If all tasks are closed or remaining tasks are blocked, respond with DONE on the last line."
    ]

    // --- Edges ---
    start -> pick_task

    pick_task -> investigate [label="MORE", condition="preferred_label=MORE"]
    pick_task -> done        [label="DONE", condition="preferred_label=DONE"]

    investigate -> implement -> run_tests -> verify

    verify -> close_task [label="PASS", condition="preferred_label=PASS"]
    verify -> fixup      [label="FAIL", condition="preferred_label=FAIL"]
    fixup  -> verify

    close_task -> check_remaining

    check_remaining -> pick_task [label="MORE", condition="preferred_label=MORE", loop_restart=true]
    check_remaining -> done      [label="DONE", condition="preferred_label=DONE"]
}
